sentence: Michele Ann Marie "Shelley" Fabares (; born January 19, 1944) is an American actress and singer.

She is best known for her television roles as Mary Stone on the sitcom The Donna Reed Show (1958–1963) and as Christine Armstrong on the sitcom Coach (1989–97), the latter of which earned her two Primetime Emmy Awards nominations.

She is the niece of actress Nanette Fabray (née Fabares).

Her father was James Alan Fabares, who was born in Algiers, New Orleans on 2 August 1909, and died in Los Angeles on 10 December 1977, and her mother was Elsa R. Eyler, who died from Alzheimer's disease in 1992.
At the age of 10, she made her first appearance on television in an episode of Letter to Loretta, "The Clara Schuman Story" (1954).

On TV she was in Captain Midnight, Annie Oakley, Fury, and Colgate Theatre.
